1
00:00:01,020 --> 00:00:05,600
Hello guys, in the following minutes I want
to discuss the basics of the position trading,

2
00:00:05,600 --> 00:00:11,219
the advantages of adopting this trading style
and we will also see 3 position trading strategies

3
00:00:11,219 --> 00:00:14,170
you could implement right away.

4
00:00:14,170 --> 00:00:18,780
Position trading is a trading technique which
looks at the bigger picture of the market,

5
00:00:18,780 --> 00:00:23,950
usually involving a combination of technical
analysis and fundamental analysis.

6
00:00:23,950 --> 00:00:29,610
When evaluating the markets, position traders
usually make their research on weekly and

7
00:00:29,610 --> 00:00:31,190
monthly price charts.

8
00:00:31,190 --> 00:00:39,550
I’m sure you already know that 95% of all
traders lose money and only 5% of them make

9
00:00:39,550 --> 00:00:41,550
any real money.

10
00:00:41,550 --> 00:00:46,590
This is due to the fact that the majority
of traders enter the markets with a “get

11
00:00:46,590 --> 00:00:48,610
rich quick” mentality.

12
00:00:48,610 --> 00:00:53,850
Short-term trading can be profitable, but
on the long run you’ll be safer when adopting

13
00:00:53,850 --> 00:00:56,600
a position trading attitude.

14
00:00:56,600 --> 00:01:00,969
When executed correctly, position trading
comes with several advantages:

15
00:01:00,969 --> 00:01:06,810
The most important advantage of the position
trading eliminates market noise

16
00:01:06,810 --> 00:01:12,939
Sometimes when trading on shorter time frames
you get caught up in the market price fluctuations,

17
00:01:12,939 --> 00:01:16,709
rumors or the constant monitoring of the market.

18
00:01:16,709 --> 00:01:18,579
That’s market noise.

19
00:01:18,579 --> 00:01:23,399
Position trading on higher time frames will
help you to remove the market noise and to

20
00:01:23,399 --> 00:01:26,979
extract the correct information from the price.

21
00:01:26,979 --> 00:01:32,200
Another advantage is the flexibility
While day traders monitor the price action

22
00:01:32,200 --> 00:01:38,700
very closely and their “screen time” is
considerably higher, position traders don’t

23
00:01:38,700 --> 00:01:41,219
have to deal with such problems.

24
00:01:41,219 --> 00:01:46,240
Position trading offers time away from charts.

25
00:01:46,240 --> 00:01:52,419
Also, position traders execute fewer trades
and they don’t have to monitor the trades

26
00:01:52,419 --> 00:01:53,780
all the time.

27
00:01:53,780 --> 00:01:58,679
Another advantage of the position trading
is that you don’t over trade

28
00:01:58,679 --> 00:02:04,270
Position trading keeps you away from the daily
“temptations” of entering and exiting

29
00:02:04,270 --> 00:02:08,099
the market many times thought the day.

30
00:02:08,099 --> 00:02:13,090
Position traders do not trade actively and
execute fewer trades.

31
00:02:13,090 --> 00:02:19,120
Also, position traders don’t have to deal
with the daily stress arising from trading,

32
00:02:19,120 --> 00:02:25,890
that’s because their positions have plenty
of room to survive the market volatility.

33
00:02:25,890 --> 00:02:31,170
Another important advantage of position trading
is the fact that signals are more relevant

34
00:02:31,170 --> 00:02:35,420
on higher time frames
Position traders often use the daily, weekly

35
00:02:35,420 --> 00:02:36,850
and monthly charts.

36
00:02:36,850 --> 00:02:40,630
They are not interested in analyzing lower
time frames.

37
00:02:40,630 --> 00:02:44,920
This adds weight to their trading systems.

38
00:02:44,920 --> 00:02:51,180
A divergence is much stronger on the weekly
chart than on a 15-minute chart.

39
00:02:51,180 --> 00:02:57,760
A moving average crossover has more relevance
on the daily chart than on the 5-minute chart.

40
00:02:57,760 --> 00:03:05,180
By using higher time frames position traders
improve the quality of their trades.

41
00:03:05,180 --> 00:03:10,100
Now that we discussed the advantages of position
trading, let’s see a couple of strategies

42
00:03:10,100 --> 00:03:11,900
used by position traders.

43
00:03:11,900 --> 00:03:17,810
An efficient position trading strategy is
divergence trading on the weekly/monthly charts.

44
00:03:17,810 --> 00:03:23,670
Divergences are more reliable on higher time
frames because the market does not move as

45
00:03:23,670 --> 00:03:26,890
fast and it is easier to define trends.

46
00:03:26,890 --> 00:03:33,290
By trading divergences, the position traders
see the patterns developing and have time

47
00:03:33,290 --> 00:03:35,100
to make the correct decisions.

48
00:03:35,100 --> 00:03:40,960
In this weekly gold chart, we spotted an excellent
hidden divergence opportunity.

49
00:03:40,960 --> 00:03:49,010
The gold price recorded a strong upward trend
and retraced to the 23.6 Fibonacci retracement

50
00:03:49,010 --> 00:03:50,010
level.

51
00:03:50,010 --> 00:03:56,470
During this time, a hidden divergence pattern
developed on the stochastic oscillator.

52
00:03:56,470 --> 00:04:03,100
This represented a perfect buy for a position
trader, the gold price continuing its upward

53
00:04:03,100 --> 00:04:05,040
trend.

54
00:04:05,040 --> 00:04:09,240
A similar pattern is seen in this aussie dollar
weekly chart.

55
00:04:09,240 --> 00:04:17,609
After 4 months of price increases, the market
retraced to 38.2 fib level.

56
00:04:17,609 --> 00:04:25,349
The stochastic indicator showed a hidden divergence
around that area, representing a good buy

57
00:04:25,349 --> 00:04:27,669
opportunity for a position trader.

58
00:04:27,669 --> 00:04:35,150
The price indeed rejected that area and continued
its upward trend for the rest of the year.

59
00:04:35,150 --> 00:04:39,789
On the Apple stock chart, we found this pattern
once again.

60
00:04:39,789 --> 00:04:44,729
The Apple price was in a strong upward trend
on the weekly chart.

61
00:04:44,729 --> 00:04:48,499
The price retraced to 38.2 fib level.

62
00:04:48,499 --> 00:04:54,599
This move, combined with the hidden divergence
on the stochastic oscillator represented a

63
00:04:54,599 --> 00:04:58,009
great opportunity for a position trader.

64
00:04:58,009 --> 00:05:03,490
As you can observe from these examples, the
hidden divergences represent a reliable tool

65
00:05:03,490 --> 00:05:09,949
for position traders on the higher time frames,
generating high probability signals.

66
00:05:09,949 --> 00:05:13,560
Another viable strategy for a position trader
is the carry trade.

67
00:05:13,560 --> 00:05:19,879
The carry trade is an interesting forex long-term
strategy that is based on the difference in

68
00:05:19,879 --> 00:05:21,082
interest rates around the world.

69
00:05:21,082 --> 00:05:27,639
It’s a strategy through which a position
trader sells a certain currency with a low-interest

70
00:05:27,639 --> 00:05:34,100
rate and uses the funds to buy a currency
with higher interest rate.

71
00:05:34,100 --> 00:05:39,779
By executing a carry trade, the position trader
intends to generate profit from the difference

72
00:05:39,779 --> 00:05:42,809
in interest rates between two countries.

73
00:05:42,809 --> 00:05:48,909
Also, with an appropriate approach, the position
trader aims to benefit not only from the difference

74
00:05:48,909 --> 00:05:53,699
in interest rates but also from the changes
in the exchange rate.

75
00:05:53,699 --> 00:06:00,490
Here’s an example, the Aussie dollar/ and
the Japanese yen on the monthly timeframe.

76
00:06:00,490 --> 00:06:06,539
That’s a good carry trade opportunity because
there is a big difference between interest

77
00:06:06,539 --> 00:06:12,770
rates of the 2 countries, so we could make
a profit in the long term from the swap.

78
00:06:12,770 --> 00:06:18,659
After we determined the main monthly relevant
support and resistance and potential price

79
00:06:18,659 --> 00:06:24,650
patterns we identified a possible long position
in the direction of the prevailing upward

80
00:06:24,650 --> 00:06:30,300
trend, after the price rejected the 38.2 fib
level.

81
00:06:30,300 --> 00:06:35,639
A long entry on the currency pair would be
a safe entry, considering the long term.

82
00:06:35,639 --> 00:06:42,750
The long position on the instrument is related
to a positive swap, and thus the profit of

83
00:06:42,750 --> 00:06:50,150
such a transaction would be even greater if
the currency pair will continue to move upwards.

84
00:06:50,150 --> 00:06:53,689
Another position trading strategy involves
moving averages.

85
00:06:53,689 --> 00:06:58,639
The moving averages are probably the most
well-known and heavily used indicators in

86
00:06:58,639 --> 00:07:03,960
technical analysis because they effectively
captures the trend of a financial market in

87
00:07:03,960 --> 00:07:07,139
an easily identifiable manner.

88
00:07:07,139 --> 00:07:11,810
Position traders often use moving averages
for identifying and confirming support and

89
00:07:11,810 --> 00:07:13,440
resistance levels.

90
00:07:13,440 --> 00:07:19,389
A crossover between 2 moving average is probably
one of the most well-known technical analysis

91
00:07:19,389 --> 00:07:21,569
signal used by traders.

92
00:07:21,569 --> 00:07:28,599
The strategy is simple, position traders trade
moving averages, one with a shorter period

93
00:07:28,599 --> 00:07:35,500
and the other with a longer period and track
the signals when a crossover occurs.

94
00:07:35,500 --> 00:07:41,330
This is the simplest position trading strategy
because moving average crossovers on higher

95
00:07:41,330 --> 00:07:46,499
timeframes work better than short-term crossovers.

96
00:07:46,499 --> 00:07:50,080
This is likely because they produce fewer
false signals.

97
00:07:50,080 --> 00:07:56,619
However, be careful with moving average crossovers,
because this strategy works only in trending

98
00:07:56,619 --> 00:07:57,619
markets.

99
00:07:57,619 --> 00:08:03,699
When the market is in a range, you’ll probably
see something similar on your charts.

100
00:08:03,699 --> 00:08:08,740
Despite the fact that position trading is
a long-term strategy and takes some time to

101
00:08:08,740 --> 00:08:15,020
profit from markets, it’s a safer alternative
compared to the other strategies in the market.

102
00:08:15,020 --> 00:08:21,349
Used it in conjunction with the long-term
trend and with a proper money management system,

103
00:08:21,349 --> 00:08:26,559
the position trading might bring back the
enjoyment of trading, without having to spend

104
00:08:26,559 --> 00:08:29,909
all day in front of the computer.

105
